node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU2MTgwMjg1NTg=", "number": 11, "title": "Why is the gate oscillator low-pass filtered", "user": {"login": "vsariola", "id": 5684185, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODQxODU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5684185?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola", "html_url": "https://github.com/vsariola", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2020-05-14T08:24:47Z", "updated_at": "2020-05-14T10:32:00Z", "closed_at": "2020-05-14T10:32:00Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI'm wondering why is the gate oscillator low-pass filtered. Specifically, I'm referring to these [lines](https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/blob/e28554120325fcaaebbe8189eef16b57fd83f0a8/4klang_source/4klang.asm#L428). I rewrote the comments to understand what is happening:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfld     dword [WRK+go4kVCO_wrk.gatestate] ; g x, g is gatestate, x is the input to this filter 0/1\r\nfsub    st1                               ; g-x x\r\nfmul    dword [c_dc_const]                ; c(g-x) x\r\nfaddp   st1, st0                          ; x+c(g-x)\r\nfst     dword [WRK+go4kVCO_wrk.gatestate] ; g'=x+c(g-x)\r\n;\r\n; Another way to look at this (remembering that c~0.996)  \r\n; g'=cg+(1-c)x\r\n; output g'\r\n```\r\nThat is a low-pass filter / exponentially decaying moving average of x. I'm looking at the waveforms outputted by the gate and for sure they low-pass filtered versions of the input (gate bit).\r\n\r\nWhy generate an interesting gate signal and then filter all the interesting details away? Maybe gate was meant only for LFOs and this is to slightly smooth the signal?\r\n\r\nOr maybe the point was to have a highpass filter i.e. to remove DC-offset? Then the code should return x-g' instead of g'.\r\n", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/11/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/11/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed", "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/10", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/10/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/10/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/10/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/pull/10", "id": 612791084, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDEzNjY4OTAz", "number": 10, "title": "Add the files required to run 4klang on Linux", "user": {"login": "xyproto", "id": 52813, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUyODEz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/52813?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto", "html_url": "https://github.com/xyproto", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyproto/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2020-05-05T18:02:16Z", "updated_at": "2022-02-27T17:55:24Z", "closed_at": "2022-02-27T17:55:23Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/pulls/10", "html_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/pull/10", "diff_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/pull/10.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/pull/10.patch", "merged_at": "2022-02-27T17:55:23Z"}, "body": "* Build with `make`.\r\n* Run with `make run`.\r\n\r\nI also made the 64-bit version compile, but it segfaults at run (use the sed lines in the `Makefile` that are commented out to try it out).\r\n\r\nTested on 64-bit Arch Linux with yasm 1.3.0 and gcc 9.3.0.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/10/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/10/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/9", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/9/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/9/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/9/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/9", "id": 609778680, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU2MDk3Nzg2ODA=", "number": 9, "title": "Unnecessary code: short jump to next line", "user": {"login": "vsariola", "id": 5684185, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODQxODU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5684185?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola", "html_url": "https://github.com/vsariola", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-04-30T10:00:11Z", "updated_at": "2022-02-26T10:22:54Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/blob/e28554120325fcaaebbe8189eef16b57fd83f0a8/4klang_source/4klang.asm#L1497\r\n\r\nMy understanding is that this short jump to next line is unnecessary.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/9/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/9/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/8", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/8/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/8/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/8/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/8", "id": 605399396, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU2MDUzOTkzOTY=", "number": 8, "title": "Unnecessary code in Power-function", "user": {"login": "vsariola", "id": 5684185, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODQxODU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5684185?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola", "html_url": "https://github.com/vsariola", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-04-23T09:56:12Z", "updated_at": "2020-04-23T10:41:31Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "In 4klang.asm, the [lines 251-253](https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/blob/e28554120325fcaaebbe8189eef16b57fd83f0a8/4klang_source/4klang.asm#L251) are:\r\n```asm\r\nfld1\r\nfadd\tst0\t\r\nfyl2x\r\n```\r\nI believe they do absolutely nothing to the stack and can be removed. To see this, I added some comments:\r\n\r\n```asm\r\n         ; Stack: x\r\nfld1     ; Stack: 1 x\r\nfadd st0 ; Stack: 2 x\r\nfyl2x    ; Stack: x*log2(2)      ... which is *drumfill* just x\r\n```\r\nI think they are a left-over from a time when the power function could compute any power, not just 2^x. Also, I'm just learning x86 assembly so there could be something I'm missing here; however, I just ran some regression tests after deleting these three lines and all my regression tests seem to pass.\r\n\r\nAlso, the comments seem to be completely off, I think better comments could be:\r\n```asm\r\n              ; x\r\nfld1          ; 1 x\r\nfadd st0      ; 2 x\r\nfyl2x         ; x // until this line could be completely removed?\r\nfld1          ; 1 x\r\nfld st1       ; x 1 x\r\nfprem         ; mod(x,1) 1 x\r\nf2xm1         ; 2^mod(x,1)-1 1 x\r\nfaddp st1,st0 ; 2^mod(x,1) x\r\nfscale        ; 2^mod(x,1)*2^trunc(x) x\r\n              ; Equal to:\r\n              ; 2^x x\r\nfstp st1      ; 2^x\r\nret\r\n```", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/8/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/8/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/7", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/7/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/7/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/7/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/7", "id": 595916122, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1OTU5MTYxMjI=", "number": 7, "title": "Incorrect GO4K_FSTG_ID\twhen exporting songs that don't use glitch", "user": {"login": "vsariola", "id": 5684185, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODQxODU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5684185?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola", "html_url": "https://github.com/vsariola", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2020-04-07T14:34:50Z", "updated_at": "2020-04-07T14:34:50Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Working on the current master branch.\r\n\r\nWhen exporting a song with a global store and without a glitch, in the exported .inc file GO4K_FSTG_ID is set to 13 but should be 12, because there is no glitch op code and thus _go4kFSTG_func is at index 12 in the go4k_synth_commands table. [See here](https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/blob/e28554120325fcaaebbe8189eef16b57fd83f0a8/4klang_source/4klang.asm#L90)\r\n\r\n The 'else' branch (that adds filler in case glitch is not used) was removed on purpose to maintain compatibility with pre-glitch songs, but the current [exporter](https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/blob/e28554120325fcaaebbe8189eef16b57fd83f0a8/4klang_source/Go4kVSTi/source/GoSynth/Go4kVSTiCore.cpp#L2721) always exports GO4K_FSTG_ID as 13.\r\n\r\nThe 4klang.asm version in Go4kVSTI/win directory works by adding the filler but in the process breaks compatibility.\r\n\r\nShort term solution is to export GO4K_FSTG_ID as 12 if glitch is not used, and 13 if glitch is used.\r\n\r\nHowever, would it be possible to not include the function pointers in the go4k_synth_commands in case a particular unit is not used? This should even save a few bytes, right? And then give all units IDs accordingly in a running manner in the exported .inc file, in case the unit was used.\r\n", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/7/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/7/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/6", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/6/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/6/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/6/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/6", "id": 595397261, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1OTUzOTcyNjE=", "number": 6, "title": "Crashes during export (3.2.2-master)", "user": {"login": "vsariola", "id": 5684185, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODQxODU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5684185?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola", "html_url": "https://github.com/vsariola", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vsariola/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-04-06T20:14:12Z", "updated_at": "2020-04-06T20:40:53Z", "closed_at": "2020-04-06T20:40:53Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Using the current 4klang 3.2.2 from master, recording fails when exporting a local STORE command (target: LOAD) in a global instrument. \r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce**: Load the offending patch (attached) in 4klang, try recording anything. I used 16-bit output if that has any significance.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**: The .inc file is created as expected.\r\n\r\n**Observed behavior**: 4klang crashes and takes the host with it. The last lines in the exported .inc file are:\r\n...\r\n```\r\nGO4K_BEGIN_PARAMDEF(Global)\r\n\tGO4K_ACC\tACCTYPE(AUX)\r\n\tGO4K_DLL\tPREGAIN(128),DRY(128),FEEDBACK(96),DAMP(64),FREQUENCY(0),DEPTH(0),DELAY(19),COUNT(1)\r\n\tGO4K_FOP\tOP(FOP_XCH)\r\n\tGO4K_DLL\tPREGAIN(128),DRY(128),FEEDBACK(96),DAMP(64),FREQUENCY(0),DEPTH(0),DELAY(19),COUNT(1)\r\n\tGO4K_FOP\tOP(FOP_XCH)\r\n\tGO4K_VCF\tFREQUENCY(76),RESONANCE(32),VCFTYPE(BANDPASS|STEREO)\r\n\tGO4K_FLD\tVALUE(65)\r\n\tGO4K_FOP\tOP(FOP_ADDP)\r\n\tGO4K_FST\tAMOUNT(128),DEST(14*MAX_UNIT_SLOTS+0+\r\n```\r\n\r\n...that's it, that's where it ends. Looking at the source, I assume it crashes [here](https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/blob/e28554120325fcaaebbe8189eef16b57fd83f0a8/4klang_source/Go4kVSTi/source/GoSynth/Go4kVSTiCore.cpp#L3270). Wtf? modes.c_str() returns an invalid string? \r\n\r\nRunning on windows 10, 64-bit, inside renoise 3.2.1.\r\n\r\n[offending_patch.zip](https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/files/4440526/offending_patch.zip)\r\n\r\n\r\n", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/6/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/6/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed", "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/5", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/5/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/5/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/5/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/hzdgopher/4klang/issues/5", "id": 510505403, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1MTA1MDU0MDM=", "number": 5, "title": "64 bit player?", "user": {"login": "kode54", "id": 796316, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjc5NjMxNg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/796316?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54", "html_url": "https://github.com/kode54", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kode54/received_eve